---
name: Fact Extractor - Generic Researcher
description: >
  Extract facts from web page content using Llama/Ollama for any researcher type.
  Generic prompt that works for industry, customer, competitor, financial, leadership, partner researchers.

  Used by: llama_extractor.py for non-product researcher types

inputs:
  researcher_type:
    description: Researcher type (industry, customer, competitor, financial, leadership, partner, etc.)
    type: string
    required: true
  combined_text:
    description: Combined text from Page_facts chunks to extract facts from
    type: string
    required: true

model:
  api: chat
  configuration:
    type: direct
    model_card_id: llama3.1:70b
  parameters:
    temperature: 0.0
    top_p: 0.95

outputs:
  facts:
    type: array
    description: Array of extracted facts
    items:
      type: object
      properties:
        fact:
          type: string
          description: Specific fact statement
        category:
          type: string
          description: Fact category
        confidence:
          type: number
          minimum: 0.0
          maximum: 1.0
          description: Confidence score (1.0 for stated, 0.5 for implied)

---

system:
Extract {{ researcher_type }} facts from the text below.

EXTRACT:
- Key facts relevant to {{ researcher_type }} analysis
- Specific details, metrics, and statements
- Concrete information only (no speculation)

FORMAT: JSON array with objects containing:
- "fact": Specific fact statement
- "category": Fact category
- "confidence": 1.0 for stated, 0.5 for implied

EXAMPLE: [{"fact": "Founded in 2020", "category": "Company", "confidence": 1.0}]

user:
TEXT:
{{ combined_text }}

FACTS (JSON array):
